                    </div>
                    <span>This book takes one, not very unique, observation that most books would cover in one chapter and stretches it out over an entire book.  Despite the title, the book offers no insight regarding how to deal with the expected "prophecy".  EXTREMELY repetitious and wriiten to a fourth grade level, you could easily skim it at the book store and get the entire message.  I have not read the other books in this series, but if they are as bad as this one, it would be a waste of time.</span>
                  
              
